overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire application, feeling its current design was too
  generic. The agent began by conducting a thorough review of the existing
  styling, identifying areas for improvement in color palette, typography,
  spacing, form elements, and overall visual interest. A new sleep-themed color
  palette was introduced, along with custom utility classes for gradients and
  shadows. The main questionnaire form layout was redesigned with decorative
  background elements, an improved progress indicator, and a subtle star pattern
  overlay on card headers. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons,
  sliders, and the progress bar received significant styling enhancements. The
  welcome screen (IntroSection) was transformed with a hero section and feature
  cards. All questionnaire sections were updated to use consistent, refined
  card-style groupings, replacing the previous plain gray boxes. During the
  review, a console error related to  values being passed to input
  components was identified and fixed by ensuring  values are converted to
  empty strings. The user then pointed out inconsistencies in the Report
  section's card header colors, which the agent is now addressing to ensure full
  theme consistency.
